detailedReviews.author: Brian VanTilburg
detailedReviews.text: I was craving a Chicago deep dish pizza & didn't want to drive all the way to Giordanos, so I did a search & it gave me this place. I'm glad it did. The pizza was amazing.  I hadn't heard of this place & plan on coming back to dine in.  The bartender who helped me was very friendly.

detailedReviews.author: James Digit
detailedReviews.text:
Okay, they genuinely earned this good review. Hard.

I ordered a door dash. About 50 minutes later, a dasher arrives with the wrong order. I didn't notice right away because there was a pizza and a large garlic... something that I thought was mine. 30 seconds later, I realized it was wrong and called Door Dash who wanted to do very little. Door Dash doesn't have a big office with folks taking phone calls, so I was PISSED. Called this location to complain and was STILL pissed.

Threw everything in the car which is what I was trying to avoid since it was late in the day, and drove over to the Rich St one (the one I ordered from over at the Trolly closed for the day while it was being delivered). A manager came up and I started yelling. Hell, I would've started throwing napkins and straws and whatnot. But I encountered a decent manager that did everything he could to calm me down. I did because it was nice to have a person talking to me rationally after a long day.

He asks what my order was, lets me know he'll get it all taken care of. He did!

As for the food? FABULOUS. Large pizza, pie style cut with a thin crust (neapolitan style), well cooked, and a garlic bread. All of it quite worthy. I should go here more often, and given their attitudes and incredibly professional demeanor while looking quite casual is the type of local shop that deserves infinite respect!!

Sorry for giving anyone here a bad experience, and thank you endlessly for handling the Door Dash mistake with utmost respect and care. This is a business that is ready to do business. If it ain't right, they will strive to make it right! Classy, and damn good pizza.

detailedReviews.text: Kitchen was behind both times I've ordered. The short guy bartender was rude and dismissive both times I've gone. Calzone was good albeit very cheesy. Pizza was good! Ingredients are good quality in general. None of it was worth the money but that's what coupons are for.

detailedReviews.author: Katherine Burke
detailedReviews.text:
I got The Dragon pizza and a Caesar salad. The Caesar dressing tasted HEAVILY of nutritional yeast, and it overwhelmed the other flavors. I actually really like the flavor of nutritional yeast, and put it on lots of things at home, but whatever was going on with this dressing made it not taste like Caesar at all, and it was off-putting. The large shavings of Parmesan in the salad were rubbery and unpleasant to chew. The croutons were great.

The pros of the pizza: it had one million pepperonis, which is awesome, and the edge crust was crispy and delicious. The cons: the pepperoni layer was directly on the (veryyyyyyyy limp, soggy, and floppy) crust, and when I lifted it, the entire layer of toppings peeled away and fell forward from the crust edge and fell entirely off the pizza in one sheet. The cheese is on top of the pepperoni, with none underneath. I‚Äôve never had that happen with a pizza. After I put the sheet of toppings back on and tried again carefully, it did it again but this time it all ended up sliding off onto the floor before I could catch it. This happened with all the pieces I tried to eat. I eventually gave up.
The pepperonis, while wonderfully abundant on the pizza, had a sharp burnt plastic flavor that was really unappealing, and the majority of the crust was soggy and had a slimy texture where the toppings met the crust.

My food was $35, so I was super disappointed. I won‚Äôt be going back even though it‚Äôs right by where I live. I absolutely wasted my money.

positive.author: Ryan (Rye105)
positive.text: We love Yellow Brick Pizza! Great location and the dinning room is a total vibe.  We recommend the Dragon pizza!

neutral.author: andrew fisher
neutral.text: Wait was long. The Ceasar salad was good. I ordered a buffalo chicken calzone. While the dough was fantastic the chicken was grey and tasted disgusting. Would recommend sticking to their pizza or salad. Great atmosphere thought!

neutral.author: Tricia
neutral.text: The garlic knots were delicious. As was the build your own bacon and cheese pizza my son had was cooked perfectly and loaded with bacon. However the pizza I got, the quartoro formaggi, was so soggy the crust not just dripped, but folded over on itself and fell apart trying to pick up a piece. The flavor was really good but unfortunately the entire texture of the pizza was drenched and falling apart.

neutral.author: C Porter
neutral.text: Thier garlic cheese knots were üî•!! On point with those, delicious!! Thier deep dish Chicago pizza was, uh, yuk!! Took 40 min, was cold, cheese was rubber, and way to much sauce. The staff was amazing.  A+ to staff, great job. I advise if you want to visit, get the garlic cheese knots. Besides that, hard pass. Again great staff. LGBTQ+ friendly. A good plus. Walls were dirty, needs cleaned. Floors need better clean care. But the staff again WAS AMAZING!!

negative.author: David Hall
negative.text: Not great. Pizza was runny. Server was the bartender and pre occupied. Walking under the scary bridge from downtown is terrifying at night. Like a horror movie.

negative.author: randy garrison
negative.text: Ordered a calzone and had a sauce with stuff i didn't want, nowhere on menu does it describe the sauce. No offer to take it off menu or reduce the price for food I couldn't eat.
